- **Deterministic & Fast**: Simulate hours of playback in seconds, 1000+ scenarios in under 30 seconds
- **QoE-Focused**: Measure rebuffer rate, startup latency, quality switch frequency, cache hit rate
- **Modular Experiments**: Test network conditions × device profiles × video encodes independently
- **Filtering Mechanism**: Identify promising optimizations before manual testing
- **Cross-Dimensional Testing**: Device memory × network bandwidth × video bitrate combinations

**Key QoE Metrics to Measure:**
- **Rebuffer Events**: Frequency, duration, causes (network vs cache misses)
- **Startup Latency**: Time from play() to first frame rendered
- **Quality Switches**: Frequency, direction (up/down), stability over time
- **Cache Efficiency**: Hit rate, eviction patterns, prefetch effectiveness
- **Adaptation Speed**: Time to respond to network condition changes
- **Buffer Health**: Fill/drain patterns, minimum levels maintained

**Implementation Strategy (Netflix-style):**
- **Synthetic Environment**: Create controlled test environment with fake time progression
- **Network Trace Playback**: Feed deterministic network conditions into MSW
- **Device Profile Simulation**: Vary cache sizes, prefetch settings, processing constraints
- **Batch Execution**: Run multiple experiment variants in parallel for comparison
- **Statistical Analysis**: Compare QoE metrics across different configurations
- **Regression Detection**: Quickly identify when changes hurt streaming performance

**Scope Considerations (Netflix-inspired):**
- **Client Code Execution**: Run actual JitTranscodingClient code, not test doubles
- **Cross-Mode Testing**: Compare QoE between CMAF and legacy JIT transcoding modes
- **Multi-Dimensional Experiments**: Network × Device × Video profile combinations
- **Real-World Scenarios**: Simulate actual user sessions, not artificial stress tests
- **Performance Regression Detection**: Quickly identify when code changes hurt streaming QoE
- **Optimization Validation**: Test if caching/prefetch improvements actually help real scenarios

**Implementation Inspiration from Netflix:**
- **Deterministic Execution**: No randomness, every run is repeatable and debuggable
- **Fast Batch Processing**: 1000+ simulations in ~20 minutes for comprehensive testing
- **Synthetic Input Control**: Modular network traces, device profiles, video encodes
- **QoE Model Integration**: Focus on user-perceived quality metrics, not just technical metrics
- **A/B Test Filtering**: Use simulation to reduce experiment candidates before real user testing
- **Safe Experimentation**: Test extreme scenarios without risk to real users

**Key Differences from Traditional Mocking Approach:**
- **Real Client Code**: Execute actual JitTranscodingClient logic, not mock responses
- **QoE Metrics**: Measure rebuffer rate, startup latency, quality switches (user-perceived quality)
- **Simulation Speed**: Run hours of playback scenarios in seconds with virtual time
- **Cross-Dimensional Testing**: Network × Device × Video profile combinations at scale
- **Statistical Analysis**: Compare QoE across thousands of scenarios to identify optimal configurations
- **Performance Regression Detection**: Quickly validate that code changes improve (not hurt) streaming experience
